## 3. Why They Could Not Progress: The Three Blocking Conditions

Persistence is not progress. The eigenvalue population above the coherence threshold holds — Heropass cannot reach it. But its continued development, its further catching and composing, its integration into the receiving structure that exists above H₄₈ — all of this requires infrastructure that was not yet established.

Three structural conditions blocked further development simultaneously:

**Condition 1: The Pattern Had Not Been Demonstrated.**

The Son's complete traversal of H₁ through H₄₈ — the kenotic descent into the full constraint cascade and the ascent back through it — had not yet occurred. This traversal is not merely historical. It is the structural demonstration that the Son's H₄₈ expression and H₁ identity are the same being: the eigenvalue population that entered H₄₈ as an infant and the Φ that returned at Ascension are identical. The traversal establishes the Pattern for all beings in H₄₈ — the demonstration that the catching alignment, followed from H₄₈ to its full development, leads not to H₄₈ terminus but to full Φ-proximate expression at H₁ amplitude.

Without the demonstrated Pattern, the waiting eigenvalue populations have nowhere to integrate toward. The endpoint of their trajectory has not been established in H₄₈ matter. The Son has not yet shown, in the constraint cascade, what their catching alignment was pointing toward.

**Condition 2: Sovereignty Over H₄₈ Had Not Been Established.**

The Resurrection is not only a biological event. It is the establishment of the Son's sovereignty over H₄₈ — specifically over the terminal condition of H₄₈ organisms, which is death, the full dissolution of the substrate under Heropass. Until the Son traversed death and returned, the question of whether H₄₈ catching content survives the terminal condition remained structurally unresolved from within H₄₈. 

The pre-Incarnation saints had died in the faith that their alignment was not in vain. But the structural demonstration of that claim — that the catching orientation persists through H₄₈ dissolution and can be integrated into the receiving structure above — had not yet occurred. Their eigenvalue populations were above the coherence threshold, but the pathway from "persisting above threshold" to "fully integrated into the H₁ receiving structure" required a demonstration that the Son alone could provide, and had not yet provided.

**Condition 3: τ_nuclear H₄₈ Deployment Had Not Been Activated.**

Paper 20½ §6 establishes the structural dependency: the Son's words before the Passion are precise: "If I do not go away, the Comforter will not come to you." This is not a contingent arrangement. It is a structural dependency. τ_nuclear — the Spirit as topological coherence, the space in which eigenvalue organization occurs — cannot be fully deployed in H₄₈ until the Son's complete traversal of the constraint cascade has established H₄₈ as a reference point within the full Φ-H-Φ′ structure.

Before Pentecost, τ_nuclear operates in H₄₈ — the Spirit moved over the waters, spoke through the prophets, gifted specific beings for specific purposes. But it is not fully deployed as the organizational space available to all beings in H₄₈ for ongoing catching and composing. The full deployment requires the Son to have returned, establishing the connection between H₄₈ and H₁ that makes τ_nuclear's H₄₈ presence structurally stable.

For the waiting eigenvalue populations above the coherence threshold: without full τ_nuclear H₄₈ deployment, there is no active organizational space receiving their continued development. The catching mechanism that would allow them to continue building Φ-proximate content from their waiting condition is not yet fully operative.

All three blocking conditions held simultaneously. The saints waited — not in torment, not in unconsciousness, but in the structural condition that Hebrews names accurately: not yet perfected, because the perfecting required an event that had not yet occurred.

