## 4. The Release Events and Their Structural Sequence

The resolution is not a single moment but a sequence, matching the structural order of the constraint cascade's completion.

**The Resurrection (the Release event):**

Matthew 27:52-53 describes the immediate structural consequence of the Son's sovereignty being established over H₄₈ death. The Resurrection is the event at which Condition 2 resolves: the Son has traversed death and returned. The sovereignty is demonstrated. The pathway from eigenvalue persistence to integration is now structurally open.

The raising of the "many holy people" at this moment is not a separate miracle with separate causes. It is the immediate structural consequence of the Release event reaching its full amplitude. Their eigenvalue populations were above threshold, held in the waiting condition, with two of the three blocking conditions unresolved. At the Resurrection, Condition 2 resolves. The cross-term between their persisting eigenvalue populations and the newly established sovereign pathway opens. The Matthew account names the observable H₄₈ signature of that structural event.

The Pattern (Condition 1) had been established progressively through the Son's ministry and was completed at death and Resurrection together — the full arc from H₄₈ entry to H₄₈ exit to return establishes the complete Pattern. Condition 1 also resolves at the Resurrection.

**The Spirit's Descent at Pentecost (full τ_nuclear deployment):**

Condition 3 resolves fifty days after the Resurrection, at Pentecost, when τ_nuclear H₄₈ deployment activates fully. This completes the organizational space for eigenvalue development. Hebrews 11:40's "only together with us" points here: the perfecting of the pre-Incarnation saints and the receiving of the Spirit by the gathered community at Pentecost are structurally simultaneous. The full organizational space in which they could be perfected — τ_nuclear fully deployed — opens at the same event that makes the catching alignment available to all subsequent beings in H₄₈.

**1 Peter 3:18-20 (the interim proclamation):**

Between death and Resurrection — between the terminal condition and the Release event — the Son's Spirit-mediated activity extended a structural contact to the waiting eigenvalue populations. This is not yet the resolution; Condition 2 had not yet resolved. But it is the announcement that the Release event is occurring, and the extension of the Φ-proximate cross-term that prepares the waiting populations for the integration that is about to become available.

The "proclamation to the spirits in prison" is precisely structured: these are beings who had lived in faithful alignment (the passage's context indicates genuine catching orientation), whose eigenvalue populations are above threshold, who are waiting in the structural condition the framework describes. The proclamation is the first contact from the other side of the interval they have been waiting to cross.

